g.text: You: "Let's go get the flashlight then."
You: "Looks like a gym to me."
Kim Kitsuragi: "I think you're right," he says. "Though it looks like no one's been here in ages..."
You: "No idea, Kim... but my head hurts... my head hurts *bad*."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Now, let's move on, shall we?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "No need to look for *supra-natural* explanations where a banal one will do. Now, let's move on, shall we?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "No need to look for *supra-natural* explanations where a banal one will do. Now, let's go get the flashlight, shall we?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "We don't *have to* explore an abandoned gym, you know. Besides, no one's been here in ages..."
Kim Kitsuragi: "You didn't *have* to ram the door down, you know..." He looks around. "No one's been here for ages."
You: "What if there's a *reason* why no one's been here for ages..."
Inland Empire: An eerie feeling rises in your chest...
Kim Kitsuragi: "Now, let's go get the flashlight, shall we?"
Perception (Sight): Some specks of dust shimmer in a faint beam of daylight falling from the window. Other than that, the room is dark.
You: "I think this may be the Artemitep's Boxing Club For Young Athletes."
You: "Let's just keep going, I'm sure it's just a regular abandoned house, nothing mysterious here."
Kim Kitsuragi: "No, it's a gym," he disagrees. "Though it looks like no one's been here in ages..."
Kim Kitsuragi: "I doubt the electricity still works... Good thing we have a flashlight on us. Don't forget to take it out of your bag before we move on."
Kim Kitsuragi: "I doubt the electricity still works... We should find a flashlight if we want to go on. There should be one in my Kineema."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Yes, but no one's been here in ages." He draws a stripe on the dusty floor with his foot...
Perception (Sight): Some specks of dust shimmer in a ray of streetlight falling from the window. Other than that, the room is dark.
Kim Kitsuragi: "I doubt the electricity still works... Good thing we have a flashlight on us."
You: "It's the netherworld. Beyond the veil."
